Text: RE th IAEE International Conference Cc venue I like it The th is good with me How about either Pappadeaux or Pappasito or anything else around the Kirby area Should take you guys the same amount of time getting out of downtown to beat the lunch crowd Susan nroncom To Caldwell Charles cc PM Subject RE th IAEE International Conference I am free for lunch on Ill see if Fraziers available Why dont we choose a venue somewhere between Duke and downtown Caldwell Charles on PM To cc Subject RE th IAEE International Conference Sounds like an excellent idea Does lunch on Monday December th work for your schedules If not lets hear a counteroffer Original Message From mailto Sent Tuesday November PM To Cc Subject Re th IAEE International Conference Susan I go this email as well Unfortunately Ive been busy as well and didnt really look at it As for future matters what will be our involvement for EBAHouston events Would the two of you like to get together for lunch sometime maybe with Frazier and the other current EBA officers so we can understand our rolesdutiesfunctions a little better hey arent we both pretty big clients of a certain Houston law firm hint hint Charles Dat Susan nroncom To cc PM Subject th IAEE International Conference Does anyone know this person or his organization Is this something our membership might be interested in Frankly I have been too busy to think about this if you have any comments lets talk Susan Scott Forwarded by Susan ScottETSEnron on PM Gurcan Gulen HEDU on AM To cc Subject th IAEE International Conference About three weeks ago I inquired about EBAs interest in organizing a concurrent session at the upcoming IAEE International Association for Energy Economics conference in Houston April Since I did not hear back from you I assume that EBA was not interested It would help us a lot in our future planning if you could perhaps help me with your reasoning Did we approach you too late given the Dec deadline We required all participants to pay registration fees was that an issue We couldnt guarantee you a slot even if you proposed a session was that an issue Thanks in advance for your response S Gurcan Gulen PhD Research Associate
